The paper deals with the practical challenges of adapting software quality models, which is a topic closely related to software engineering (cs.SE). The approach proposed in the paper involves the use of tools, which suggests a focus on computational methods and algorithms, making categories such as cs.CY (computational geometry) and cs.PL (programming languages) also likely. The paper also involves empirical investigation, which suggests a focus on data analysis and machine learning, making categories such as cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.SI (social and information networks) possible as well.
